1
00:00:01,921 --> 00:00:03,564
So here we are standing.

2
00:00:04,766 --> 00:00:05,748
Standing tall.

3
00:00:06,730 --> 00:00:08,394
Lifting up to the top of the head.

4
00:00:09,936 --> 00:00:16,629
Chin goes in a little.

5
00:00:16,649 --> 00:00:17,670
Relax the shoulders.

6
00:00:20,356 --> 00:00:21,277
Relax the jaw.

7
00:00:23,102 --> 00:00:24,704
Lips together, teeth apart.

8
00:00:28,178 --> 00:00:31,021
It helps to bend the legs a little to relieve the back.

9
00:00:31,682 --> 00:00:33,345
When the legs get tired, just straighten them up.

10
00:00:36,189 --> 00:00:39,335
The eyes gazing downward about a metre or so away.

11
00:00:43,000 --> 00:00:44,844
Let us now bring our attention to the feet.

12
00:00:46,646 --> 00:00:50,051
What sensations can you feel on the soles of your feet?

13
00:01:09,944 --> 00:01:11,546
Can you distinguish two types?

14
00:01:28,370 --> 00:01:30,953
Sensations of pressure, the earth element.

15
00:01:32,375 --> 00:01:34,298
Sensations of heat, the fire element.

16
00:01:50,983 --> 00:01:58,632
can you become more aware of how the sensations in the feet are constantly changing, due mainly to the body rebalancing itself?

17
00:02:17,527 --> 00:02:24,165
In the same way, come up the body and see what sensations you can find, both on the surface and inside.

18
00:02:25,729 --> 00:02:28,938
And notice those areas where there seems to be no feeling at all.

19
00:03:26,681 --> 00:03:30,550
When you get to the scalp, do there what you did at the soles of your feet.

20
00:04:03,740 --> 00:04:05,302
Now launch your attention outward.

21
00:04:06,645 --> 00:04:19,470
Keeping the eyes gazing downward, become aware of the colours and shapes, the sounds entering your ears, the atmosphere of the room, the sense of other people.

22
00:05:17,769 --> 00:05:28,016
Open up now the awareness to include all the body sensations and feelings as well, so that the distinction between inner and outer lose their strict definition.

23
00:05:28,997 --> 00:05:32,387
It's just all one mass of sensations and feelings.

24
00:05:49,208 --> 00:05:53,211
and relax into the presenting moment, wide awake.

25
00:06:53,721 --> 00:06:57,887
Relaxing into the present moment like this, we're not trying to achieve anything.

26
00:06:59,589 --> 00:07:04,478
When we're trying to achieve something, we're doing something now for some future result.

27
00:07:06,800 --> 00:07:14,531
But being fully aware in this present moment, there's both the achieving and the result.

28
00:08:11,735 --> 00:08:17,302
Relaxing into the present moment, like this, we're not going anywhere.

29
00:08:17,322 --> 00:08:22,247
Fully aware of each moment, we lose a sense of past and future.

30
00:08:24,750 --> 00:08:27,293
So we've not come from somewhere and we're not going anywhere.

31
00:08:29,416 --> 00:08:34,283
But by being fully aware in this presenting moment, we've already arrived.

32
00:09:31,586 --> 00:09:38,217
Relaxing into the present moment like this, just receiving, there's no need to react or respond.

33
00:09:39,500 --> 00:09:43,767
So, when we are fully aware of this moment, like this, there's no need to perform.

34
00:09:44,447 --> 00:09:47,232
There's no need to be a personality, a person.

35
00:10:44,807 --> 00:10:53,586
Relaxing into the present moment, wide awake, achieving nothing, going nowhere, being nobody.

36
00:11:50,130 --> 00:11:54,460
When we're in this passive mode, we're developing four factors of awakening.

37
00:11:55,301 --> 00:12:05,861
Awareness, calmness of the body and mind, steadiness of attention or concentration, and equanimity.

38
00:12:08,052 --> 00:12:16,085
Equanimity means openness, receptiveness, receiving whatever comes to us from a place of don't know, not sure.

39
00:12:16,144 --> 00:12:33,975
This is the basic ground out of which our curiosity can rise, untainted by conceptual thinking, untainted by history, to investigate the three characteristics of existence, impermanence, unsatisfactoriness and not-self.

40
00:13:44,559 --> 00:13:48,884
In this mode of calm, quiet abiding, we can see intentions arise.

41
00:13:50,407 --> 00:13:53,009
If they're unwholesome, we can resist the temptation.

42
00:13:53,090 --> 00:13:54,371
We have time, we have space.

43
00:13:56,214 --> 00:13:59,498
If wholesome intentions arise, we can decide to empower them.

44
00:14:00,779 --> 00:14:04,543
In this very simple way, we can change ourselves for the better.

45
00:14:06,506 --> 00:14:13,554
So you can see, developing this calm abiding in the present moment can have a revolutionary effect on our lives.

46
00:14:31,642 --> 00:14:32,725
intending to sit.

